1
00:01:57,419 --> 00:01:58,447
Marcus.

2
00:02:06,276 --> 00:02:07,227
How are you?

3
00:02:08,611 --> 00:02:09,758
It's been an hour.

4
00:02:13,199 --> 00:02:14,543
I thought I'd try...

5
00:02:15,690 --> 00:02:16,797
one last time.

6
00:02:18,103 --> 00:02:20,829
You should have stayed
in San Francisco, Dr. Kogan.

7
00:02:23,957 --> 00:02:25,775
By signing
this consent form,

8
00:02:26,052 --> 00:02:28,781
you'll be donating your body
to a noble cause.

9
00:02:29,690 --> 00:02:30,639
You'd...

10
00:02:31,945 --> 00:02:33,883
have a second chance...

11
00:02:34,516 --> 00:02:37,334
through my research
to live again.

12
00:02:37,955 --> 00:02:39,301
You know
what I did.

13
00:02:40,567 --> 00:02:42,307
My brother and two cops
are dead

14
00:02:42,346 --> 00:02:43,176
because of me.

15
00:02:44,582 --> 00:02:46,715
I'm not lookin'
for a second chance.

16
00:02:51,585 --> 00:02:54,448
But I'm not the only one
with a death sentence, am I?

17
00:02:57,771 --> 00:02:59,204
Do you think
I'm gonna kill your cancer

18
00:02:59,240 --> 00:02:59,992
this permanent?

19
00:03:02,245 --> 00:03:04,344
I'm not worried
about myself.

20
00:03:06,006 --> 00:03:09,364
I'm worried about
the future of the human race.

21
00:03:10,812 --> 00:03:12,282
I'll sell it to you.

22
00:03:14,329 --> 00:03:15,335
For what?

23
00:03:15,912 --> 00:03:17,241
A kiss.

24
00:03:34,447 --> 00:03:36,430
So that's what
death tastes like.

25
00:03:54,002 --> 00:03:56,253
You are doing something
very noble.

26
00:03:56,691 --> 00:03:57,956
I'm guilty.

27
00:03:58,628 --> 00:04:00,448
Just cut me up
until there's nothing left.

28
00:04:06,460 --> 00:04:09,345
That I walk through the valley
of the Shadow of Death.

29
00:04:09,940 --> 00:04:11,364
I will fear no evil.

30
00:04:11,997 --> 00:04:13,499
For thou art with me,

31
00:04:14,290 --> 00:04:17,890
thy rod and my staff,
they comfort me.

32
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,628
Do you have
any last words?

33
00:06:08,499 --> 00:06:10,139
<i>Bag Art,
this is Black Hawk Six.</i>

34
00:06:10,174 --> 00:06:11,959
<i>Missile imbound to
Skynet target.</i>

35
00:06:12,015 --> 00:06:15,173
<i>TTO 11 seconds,
taken close.</i>

36
00:06:47,790 --> 00:06:49,969
- Come on, come on!
- Move, move!

37
00:06:49,986 --> 00:06:52,086
- Help, go back!
- Right here!

38
00:07:03,548 --> 00:07:05,312
<i>Connor is on the ground.</i>

39
00:07:09,402 --> 00:07:11,220
This mission
is a quick in-and-out.

40
00:07:11,418 --> 00:07:13,475
Command teams the information
on those computers

41
00:07:13,554 --> 00:07:15,294
should be
at the highest priority.

42
00:07:48,385 --> 00:07:50,490
Connor, there's no sign
of the machines.

43
00:07:50,525 --> 00:07:51,086
They're gone.

44
00:07:51,758 --> 00:07:52,945
We too quiet.

45
00:07:52,984 --> 00:07:55,152
It's almost like
they were waiting for us.

46
00:08:15,801 --> 00:08:17,377
What the hell's
that smell, man?

47
00:08:18,565 --> 00:08:20,813
Whoa!
You're seeing this?

48
00:08:44,842 --> 00:08:47,849
Olson.
Objective located.

49
00:08:48,768 --> 00:08:50,690
There's something else
you'd have to see.

50
00:09:10,228 --> 00:09:11,846
We got what we came for,
Barbaros.

51
00:09:11,881 --> 00:09:12,926
The clock's ticking.

52
00:09:12,961 --> 00:09:14,569
Spread out,
secure the perimeter.

53
00:09:14,610 --> 00:09:16,404
I got a big gap
over here.

54
00:09:16,444 --> 00:09:18,052
Why didn't we know
about this?

55
00:09:19,741 --> 00:09:21,760
Sir, I think this is
what Command's looking for.

56
00:09:21,819 --> 00:09:23,041
I'm in
their source code.

57
00:09:23,303 --> 00:09:25,874
These people are being taken
up north to San Francisco.

58
00:09:25,993 --> 00:09:28,449
Some sort of R&D project,
for a new Terminator.

59
00:09:28,958 --> 00:09:29,958
Send it to Command.

60
00:09:31,055 --> 00:09:32,280
It's uploading,
I need two minutes.

61
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,891
Wait, wait, wait.
Go back. Go back!

62
00:09:35,088 --> 00:09:35,484
Stop!

63
00:09:41,299 --> 00:09:43,196
- T-800.
- A new Terminator.

64
00:09:45,609 --> 00:09:46,716
Thought you said
it would be...

65
00:09:47,548 --> 00:09:48,536
It's worse.

66
00:09:49,009 --> 00:09:50,613
Connor, get your nose
out of that.

67
00:09:50,648 --> 00:09:51,524
None of your business.

68
00:09:51,559 --> 00:09:52,688
You're not
leading this mission.

69
00:09:52,728 --> 00:09:55,126
Alright, let's cut
these sorry bastards loose.

70
00:09:55,161 --> 00:09:56,085
Come on, let's go!

71
00:09:56,287 --> 00:09:58,146
- Jericho, come in.
- What's that?

72
00:09:58,661 --> 00:10:00,148
Come in, Jericho.

73
00:10:00,677 --> 00:10:02,963
Connor,
get your ass top-side.

74
00:10:02,998 --> 00:10:04,856
Remind those men
they need to answer me on the radio,

75
00:10:04,891 --> 00:10:05,812
even if they're dead.

76
00:10:06,728 --> 00:10:07,558
Connor!

77
00:10:20,091 --> 00:10:21,743
<i>Connor,
get those men to respond.</i>

78
00:10:21,778 --> 00:10:23,972
Olson,
something's wrong up here.

79
00:10:35,277 --> 00:10:36,537
<i>Top-side, come in!</i>

80
00:10:40,371 --> 00:10:42,529
Help out enemy aircraft,
I'm in pursuit.

81
00:10:44,951 --> 00:10:46,918
There are human prisoners
aboard there.

82
00:10:46,953 --> 00:10:47,774
Get after 'em!

83
00:11:04,923 --> 00:11:08,308
Data transferred to plane.
Connor, we're joining you, top--

84
00:12:50,055 --> 00:12:52,539
<i>Bravo Ten, Bravo Ten.
Do you copy? Over.</i>

85
00:12:57,641 --> 00:13:00,502
<i>Eagle White to Bravo Ten.
Bravo Ten, do you copy? Over.</i>

86
00:13:04,488 --> 00:13:06,850
<i>Bravo Ten, Bravo Ten,
do you copy? Over.</i>

87
00:13:10,745 --> 00:13:11,485
Here.

88
00:13:12,176 --> 00:13:13,681
<i>Bravo Ten, identify.
Over.</i>

89
00:13:15,252 --> 00:13:16,181
Connor!

90
00:13:16,798 --> 00:13:18,263
<i>We'll send units
to the extraction point.</i>

91
00:13:18,307 --> 00:13:20,028
<i>How many survivors
are outside? Over.</i>

92
00:13:21,067 --> 00:13:21,684
One.

93
00:13:23,233 --> 00:13:24,259
<i>Copy.</i>

94
00:14:30,624 --> 00:14:31,796
Return to base, sir?

95
00:14:33,373 --> 00:14:34,325
RGB?

96
00:14:34,642 --> 00:14:37,102
Negative.
Take me to Command.

97
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:38,092
Sir.

98
00:14:39,856 --> 00:14:40,834
Command!

99
00:14:42,291 --> 00:14:43,709
Roger, re-routing.

100
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:04,258
Request
has been denied.

101
00:15:04,419 --> 00:15:06,186
Command doesn't want
to give up their position.

102
00:15:06,221 --> 00:15:07,394
Radio cogs, over.

103
00:15:07,524 --> 00:15:08,833
Are they down there?

104
00:15:09,044 --> 00:15:10,700
Request
has been denied, sir.

105
00:15:10,735 --> 00:15:13,186
Need to go home.
It's straight from the top.

106
00:15:16,428 --> 00:15:18,259
You open up that ramp!

107
00:15:18,782 --> 00:15:19,993
And you tell them...

108
00:15:20,212 --> 00:15:23,790
I need divers for a log-in.
Now!

109
00:15:27,026 --> 00:15:28,220
This is crazy.

110
00:15:56,455 --> 00:16:00,598
John Connor,
prophesied leader of the Resistance.

111
00:16:01,037 --> 00:16:03,346
Soldier, you put every man
and woman in this sub

112
00:16:03,381 --> 00:16:05,579
in jeopardy
with your little frogman stunt.

113
00:16:06,685 --> 00:16:08,332
What the hell
are you doing here?

114
00:16:08,864 --> 00:16:10,623
What did we find
down there?

115
00:16:10,658 --> 00:16:12,739
You'll be pleased down
the need-to-know basis.

116
00:16:12,774 --> 00:16:16,305
<i>Well, I need to know,
because my men died</i>

117
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:17,582
down in that hole.

118
00:16:17,617 --> 00:16:19,190
What did we find
down there?

119
00:16:19,304 --> 00:16:21,703
We found the solution,
Connor,

120
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:24,794
that can end this war,
once and for all.

121
00:16:27,872 --> 00:16:30,368
We know the machines use
short-wave transmitters

122
00:16:30,403 --> 00:16:31,385
to communicate.

123
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:35,130
Our intel has located
a hidden signal

124
00:16:35,165 --> 00:16:36,707
under
the primary channel.

125
00:16:37,251 --> 00:16:40,610
It allows for direct control
over the machines.

126
00:16:40,645 --> 00:16:43,183
Skynet's a machine,
and like all machines,

127
00:16:43,358 --> 00:16:45,107
it has an off-switch.

128
00:16:46,267 --> 00:16:47,370
Does it work?

129
00:16:47,625 --> 00:16:49,342
Will it work?
Yes.

130
00:16:49,498 --> 00:16:51,417
Have we field-tested it?
No.

131
00:16:53,145 --> 00:16:56,986
Give it to me.
I'll do it.

132
00:16:57,938 --> 00:16:59,068
I'll test it.

133
00:17:02,278 --> 00:17:03,902
Connor,
you can stay Comm unit.

134
00:17:03,937 --> 00:17:05,301
Have a nice one record.

135
00:17:06,221 --> 00:17:07,291
Alright.

136
00:17:08,419 --> 00:17:09,311
Alright.

137
00:17:11,040 --> 00:17:12,505
Leave Connor in top-side.

138
00:17:12,659 --> 00:17:13,964
Prepare for lock-out.

139
00:17:18,933 --> 00:17:20,598
Connor,
we do this right...

140
00:17:21,192 --> 00:17:22,705
The war is over.

141
00:17:23,497 --> 00:17:25,754
Remount our offensive
in 4 days.

142
00:17:29,276 --> 00:17:29,894
Connor...

143
00:17:32,478 --> 00:17:34,213
These are the codes
for the signal.

144
00:17:35,825 --> 00:17:36,591
Good luck.

145
00:17:36,850 --> 00:17:38,085
Why four days?

146
00:17:38,371 --> 00:17:41,191
A kill list was intercepted
from Skynet.

147
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:44,044
It says everyone in this room
will be dead by week's end.

148
00:17:44,751 --> 00:17:46,424
You are number two
on the list.

149
00:17:48,365 --> 00:17:49,852
Well,
who's number one?

150
00:17:50,453 --> 00:17:52,170
I don't know.
A civilian.

151
00:17:52,524 --> 00:17:54,314
Kyle. Reese.

152
00:18:34,143 --> 00:18:34,896
Barnes...

153
00:18:38,749 --> 00:18:41,464
My brother...
He didn't make it, did he?

154
00:19:30,338 --> 00:19:34,115
<i>This is tape number 28.
It's Sarah Connor to my son, John.</i>

155
00:19:34,719 --> 00:19:36,096
<i>What's most difficult
for me</i>

156
00:19:36,131 --> 00:19:38,007
<i>is trying to decide
what to tell you</i>

157
00:19:38,042 --> 00:19:39,227
<i>and what not to.</i>

158
00:19:39,709 --> 00:19:41,386
<i>Should I tell you
about your father?</i>

159
00:19:41,421 --> 00:19:42,870
<i>Will it affect
your decision</i>

160
00:19:42,905 --> 00:19:45,426
<i>to send him back in time
to protect me,</i>

161
00:19:45,753 --> 00:19:47,650
<i>knowing that
he is your father?</i>

162
00:19:48,022 --> 00:19:49,120
<i>And he'll be younger
than you,</i>

163
00:19:49,165 --> 00:19:51,165
<i>only a teenager,
when you meet him.</i>

164
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:54,092
<i>Kyle. Person could go crazy
thinking about this.</i>

165
00:19:54,878 --> 00:19:56,686
<i>But if you don't send Kyle,</i>

166
00:19:56,721 --> 00:19:59,742
<i>you can never be
and Skynet will win the war.</i>

167
00:20:04,787 --> 00:20:05,928
You want
to talk about it?

168
00:20:08,293 --> 00:20:10,420
Kyle is out there
somewhere alone

169
00:20:10,586 --> 00:20:12,144
and Skynet
is hunting him.

170
00:20:13,796 --> 00:20:14,977
What about the signal?

171
00:20:16,742 --> 00:20:17,721
What do you think?

172
00:20:27,203 --> 00:20:28,698
If it works,
it's incredible.

173
00:20:28,733 --> 00:20:29,431
Yeah.

174
00:20:29,722 --> 00:20:31,606
- We have to be careful.
- I agree.

175
00:20:32,492 --> 00:20:33,717
But we have to try.

176
00:20:33,908 --> 00:20:34,661
Okay.

177
00:20:35,918 --> 00:20:37,737
Alright then,
start with something small,

178
00:20:37,763 --> 00:20:39,169
something
more familiar with.

179
00:20:42,632 --> 00:20:44,308
We should try
to capture a Hydrobot,

180
00:20:44,343 --> 00:20:45,511
bring it in for testing.

181
00:20:45,546 --> 00:20:46,271
Yeah.

182
00:20:49,062 --> 00:20:50,108
What is it, John?

183
00:20:52,859 --> 00:20:56,076
Kill Kyle Reese,
reset the future.

184
00:20:57,420 --> 00:20:58,597
No John Connor.

185
00:21:39,253 --> 00:21:40,295
Hey!

186
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:24,563
Come with me
if you want to live.

187
00:23:30,056 --> 00:23:31,121
What is that?

188
00:23:32,609 --> 00:23:34,683
She doesn't talk,
but you need to start.

189
00:23:36,355 --> 00:23:37,396
Where did you
get that jacket?

190
00:23:38,167 --> 00:23:39,396
The other guy
didn't need it.

191
00:23:41,018 --> 00:23:44,158
You see that red?
It stands for blood.

192
00:23:44,565 --> 00:23:45,984
It's a symbol
of the Resistance.

193
00:23:46,034 --> 00:23:48,101
<i>You're obviously
not a Resistance fighter,</i>

194
00:23:48,136 --> 00:23:49,085
so take it off.

195
00:23:51,013 --> 00:23:52,087
Take it off!

196
00:23:53,550 --> 00:23:54,539
You point a gun
at someone,

197
00:23:55,017 --> 00:23:56,743
you better be ready
to pull the trigger.

198
00:24:01,591 --> 00:24:03,133
I'm going to ask you
one more time.

199
00:24:05,357 --> 00:24:06,721
What the hell was
that thing?

200
00:24:06,756 --> 00:24:07,805
A Terminator.

201
00:24:08,412 --> 00:24:09,557
T-600.

202
00:24:13,959 --> 00:24:17,675
What day is it?
What year?

203
00:24:20,424 --> 00:24:21,702
2018.

204
00:24:24,993 --> 00:24:26,151
What happened here?

205
00:24:29,211 --> 00:24:30,793
Judgement Day happened.

206
00:24:35,094 --> 00:24:36,314
I gotta get outta here.

207
00:24:37,275 --> 00:24:39,883
You can't go on foot.
Machines will cut you down.

208
00:24:40,521 --> 00:24:41,581
You need speed.

209
00:24:42,474 --> 00:24:43,393
I need a car.

210
00:24:44,039 --> 00:24:46,104
Look, there's some by
Griffith Observatory.

211
00:24:46,850 --> 00:24:48,667
- I don't know now.
- Take me.

212
00:24:50,953 --> 00:24:51,973
Get down!

213
00:25:21,317 --> 00:25:23,015
That was
a Hunter Killer.

214
00:25:24,953 --> 00:25:26,705
Thanks to you,
they know we're here.

215
00:25:29,875 --> 00:25:30,841
What's your name,
kid?

216
00:25:32,368 --> 00:25:33,476
Kyle Reese.

217
00:25:38,010 --> 00:25:38,677
Come on.

218
00:25:41,854 --> 00:25:44,842
We burn down the transmitters
so it can't talk to any of its pals

219
00:25:45,489 --> 00:25:46,790
that it can still recieve.

220
00:25:47,740 --> 00:25:48,607
Turn it on!

221
00:25:51,322 --> 00:25:52,061
You got it?

222
00:25:52,908 --> 00:25:53,831
Hold it down!
Hold a bit...

223
00:25:57,468 --> 00:25:58,677
Turn the signal up.

224
00:26:09,781 --> 00:26:10,717
Get me a strap.

225
00:26:11,756 --> 00:26:13,976
- Holy shit.
- Could you believe it?

226
00:26:15,421 --> 00:26:16,285
Just strap it tight.

227
00:26:16,560 --> 00:26:18,170
The signal
has to be continuous.

228
00:26:18,205 --> 00:26:19,544
If there's
any interruption...

229
00:26:29,514 --> 00:26:30,949
Let's rig up
a portable shortwave.

230
00:26:30,984 --> 00:26:32,990
I need to test it on
something larger in the field.

231
00:26:33,025 --> 00:26:33,637
Alright.

232
00:26:36,410 --> 00:26:37,598
Destroy this thing.

233
00:26:49,158 --> 00:26:50,405
So where are the cars?

234
00:26:50,638 --> 00:26:52,194
You don't want
to go out after dark.

235
00:26:53,063 --> 00:26:54,532
Hunter Killers have infrared.

236
00:26:54,851 --> 00:26:56,072
Hunt better at night.

237
00:26:56,947 --> 00:26:58,646
We'll all go
tomorrow morning.

238
00:27:03,559 --> 00:27:04,381
What is that?

239
00:27:04,775 --> 00:27:06,468
Two-day old coyote.

240
00:27:09,471 --> 00:27:11,345
Better than
three-day old coyote.

241
00:27:22,075 --> 00:27:23,059
Hey, hey!

242
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:30,401
- Grab it.
- What?

243
00:27:31,699 --> 00:27:32,492
Grab it.

244
00:27:42,250 --> 00:27:43,265
Magic.

245
00:27:48,750 --> 00:27:50,024
- Got it?
- Yeah.

246
00:27:51,774 --> 00:27:52,531
Thanks.

247
00:27:57,365 --> 00:27:58,469
This radio work?

248
00:27:59,556 --> 00:28:00,268
No.

249
00:28:01,632 --> 00:28:03,721
My dad
tried to fix it, but...

250
00:28:04,345 --> 00:28:05,765
He could never get it
to work.

251
00:28:22,373 --> 00:28:23,071
Hold that.

252
00:28:29,286 --> 00:28:30,555
Where is everybody?

253
00:28:31,136 --> 00:28:32,112
They're gone.

254
00:28:33,716 --> 00:28:35,048
So why are you
still here?

255
00:28:35,428 --> 00:28:38,113
'Cause we're the Resistance.
L.A. branch.

256
00:28:38,537 --> 00:28:39,982
Welcome
to the headquarters.

257
00:28:41,908 --> 00:28:42,968
Resistant to what?

258
00:28:44,809 --> 00:28:47,721
Machines.
Skynet.

259
00:28:48,095 --> 00:28:49,397
Just the two of you?

260
00:28:49,638 --> 00:28:50,329
Yeah.

261
00:28:52,484 --> 00:28:53,985
How come you're not wearing
one of these?

262
00:28:55,460 --> 00:28:57,656
'Cause I haven't
earned mine, yet.

263
00:29:07,967 --> 00:29:09,633
I hope
he's listening to this.

264
00:29:13,286 --> 00:29:14,835
We've been fighting
a long time,

265
00:29:14,870 --> 00:29:17,555
and we've all lost
so very much,

266
00:29:17,586 --> 00:29:19,009
so many loved ones gone.

267
00:29:19,476 --> 00:29:20,807
But you are
not alone.

268
00:29:21,767 --> 00:29:24,096
There are pockets of Resistance
all around the planet.

269
00:29:25,295 --> 00:29:26,416
We are at the brink...

270
00:29:28,587 --> 00:29:29,668
Do you want to see
a magic trick?

271
00:29:30,153 --> 00:29:30,904
Hold that up.

272
00:29:35,582 --> 00:29:36,499
Press the button.

273
00:29:41,216 --> 00:29:44,667
<i>If we had to finally scope
when it is less than 100 meters.</i>

274
00:29:45,321 --> 00:29:46,849
<i>We've had
a lot of firepower</i>

275
00:29:46,884 --> 00:29:48,513
<i>but the T-600's
are heavy,</i>

276
00:29:48,578 --> 00:29:50,703
<i>and so,
their primitive design.</i>

277
00:29:50,958 --> 00:29:51,834
Who is that?

278
00:29:51,869 --> 00:29:53,178
<i>If you can help
or no...</i>

279
00:29:53,229 --> 00:29:55,121
<i>- I don't know.
- then you have one option.</i>

280
00:29:55,776 --> 00:29:57,006
Their motor cortex...

281
00:29:57,327 --> 00:29:59,491
is partially exposed
to the back of their neck.

282
00:29:59,526 --> 00:30:00,018
A knife

283
00:30:00,053 --> 00:30:02,397
<i>to this area will disorient
their tracking device</i>

284
00:30:02,439 --> 00:30:03,424
<i>but not for long.</i>

285
00:30:04,359 --> 00:30:05,988
Above all,
stay alive.

286
00:30:06,134 --> 00:30:07,613
You have no idea...

287
00:30:07,657 --> 00:30:08,999
<i>how important you are</i>

288
00:30:09,334 --> 00:30:11,635
<i>and how important
you will become.</i>

289
00:30:12,140 --> 00:30:13,904
<i>The machines
are advancing even faster</i>

290
00:30:13,939 --> 00:30:15,226
<i>than I told you
they would.</i>

291
00:30:15,678 --> 00:30:17,188
<i>I've seen it
with my own eyes.</i>

292
00:30:17,223 --> 00:30:19,076
<i>They were inventing
new Terminators.</i>

293
00:30:19,685 --> 00:30:20,962
<i>New ways of killing us.</i>

294
00:30:21,576 --> 00:30:23,478
<i>Skynet is planning
something big.</i>

295
00:30:24,455 --> 00:30:26,880
<i>But the Resistance
is planning something bigger.</i>

296
00:30:29,846 --> 00:30:31,016
This is John Connor.

297
00:30:31,550 --> 00:30:32,888
<i>If you're
listening to this,</i>

298
00:30:33,865 --> 00:30:35,306
<i>you are
the Resistance.</i>

299
00:30:37,513 --> 00:30:38,759
John Connor.

300
00:30:40,959 --> 00:30:42,398
We gotta find
this guy.

301
00:31:15,882 --> 00:31:17,268
So...
You get it working?

302
00:31:18,018 --> 00:31:20,364
- Almost.
- Good.

303
00:31:21,457 --> 00:31:23,988
Look, I figure
we head east, right?

304
00:31:24,145 --> 00:31:24,992
We go
through the desert,

305
00:31:25,027 --> 00:31:26,689
then we can connect
with the Resistance there.

306
00:31:28,411 --> 00:31:29,428
I'm heading north.

307
00:31:29,681 --> 00:31:30,951
No.
No, no, no, no, no.

308
00:31:31,803 --> 00:31:34,070
The machines control
the whole Northern Sector

309
00:31:34,105 --> 00:31:35,176
upto San Francisco.

310
00:31:35,211 --> 00:31:36,477
That's Skynet's central.

311
00:31:36,681 --> 00:31:37,787
I have
to find someone.

312
00:31:37,822 --> 00:31:39,438
There's a lot
that you don't understand

313
00:31:39,473 --> 00:31:40,656
about Skynet, okay?

314
00:31:40,691 --> 00:31:42,612
It's just too dangerous
for us to go there.

315
00:31:44,627 --> 00:31:46,185
What about
the L.A. branch?

316
00:31:51,935 --> 00:31:55,604
Come on, man.
We need to get out of L.A.

317
00:32:12,603 --> 00:32:16,860
[ Song: Rooster
Band: Alice in Chains ]

318
00:32:17,214 --> 00:32:18,073
What is that?

319
00:32:19,660 --> 00:32:21,534
Something my brother
used to listen to.

320
00:32:27,482 --> 00:32:28,385
Star, get out.

321
00:32:31,731 --> 00:32:33,211
Don't look at me
like that, Star.

322
00:32:34,329 --> 00:32:35,988
Get out.
Get out!

323
00:32:39,112 --> 00:32:41,968
You're leaving?
You're gonna leave us?

324
00:32:44,620 --> 00:32:45,665
Ah, I get it.

325
00:32:48,603 --> 00:32:51,368
Do you want to know the difference
between us and the machines?

326
00:32:52,961 --> 00:32:54,847
We bury our dead.

327
00:32:56,384 --> 00:32:58,987
But no one is coming
to bury you.

328
00:33:10,027 --> 00:33:10,912
Aerostat!

329
00:33:12,268 --> 00:33:14,595
- It's a scout of a Terminator.
- Go! Drive!

330
00:33:23,640 --> 00:33:25,098
The Aerostat
heard the music.

331
00:33:28,433 --> 00:33:29,422
Keep the steering.

332
00:33:29,457 --> 00:33:31,008
I've never driven
before.

333
00:33:34,690 --> 00:33:35,472
Hold the wheel.

334
00:33:43,180 --> 00:33:44,610
This thing
is pissing me of.

335
00:33:52,733 --> 00:33:53,487
Get it!

336
00:33:54,701 --> 00:33:55,571
Hold on!

337
00:34:11,131 --> 00:34:12,823
If the idea
was to stay alive...

338
00:34:13,816 --> 00:34:14,771
I'll drive.

339
00:34:19,245 --> 00:34:21,984
We're seeing a lot of
enemy movement in L.A.

340
00:34:23,316 --> 00:34:24,623
Any of our people
in the area?

341
00:34:25,251 --> 00:34:27,775
No one on the ground.
Two A-10s in the air.

342
00:34:27,810 --> 00:34:29,390
Williams and Mirhadi.

343
00:34:29,765 --> 00:34:31,095
Send the birds down.

344
00:34:32,622 --> 00:34:34,185
Guide them
to a safe area.

345
00:34:35,351 --> 00:34:37,316
<i>Roger, Coyote 6-7
in console.</i>

346
00:34:37,351 --> 00:34:41,124
<i>Ten miles to bring.
Lima-Alpha, 1-2-5-7-9-0-3. Over.</i>

347
00:34:41,159 --> 00:34:43,039
<i>- Copy that.
- Roger, Wild Eagle.</i>

348
00:34:43,074 --> 00:34:44,073
<i>Final copy.</i>

349
00:35:41,395 --> 00:35:44,214
Hey,
there's someone here.

350
00:35:46,211 --> 00:35:47,185
Get down, now!

351
00:35:47,563 --> 00:35:48,676
- Get down! Now!
- Move!

352
00:35:48,711 --> 00:35:50,146
- Drop your weapons.
- Let's see your hands!

353
00:35:50,213 --> 00:35:51,408
I never thought
that you guys--

354
00:35:51,443 --> 00:35:52,839
- That's it, drop it!
- Move, man!

355
00:35:52,874 --> 00:35:53,574
What?

356
00:35:57,032 --> 00:35:57,917
Is there a problem?

357
00:35:58,151 --> 00:36:00,165
Hey, we saw
your Resistant sign.

358
00:36:00,200 --> 00:36:02,056
The old lady put it there,
not me.

359
00:36:03,311 --> 00:36:04,144
What do you want?

360
00:36:04,748 --> 00:36:05,761
We're looking
for fuel.

361
00:36:06,912 --> 00:36:08,096
The dark season's coming.

362
00:36:08,946 --> 00:36:10,619
We only got enough
for ourselves.

363
00:36:11,189 --> 00:36:12,551
You point that gun
at somebody,

364
00:36:12,577 --> 00:36:14,479
you better be ready
to pull the trigger.

365
00:36:17,219 --> 00:36:18,750
Put your guns down,
everyone.

366
00:36:23,435 --> 00:36:25,381
Look, we just came
to find the Resistance.

367
00:36:25,416 --> 00:36:26,101
That's all.

368
00:36:26,136 --> 00:36:28,674
The Resistance?
What a joke.

369
00:36:29,488 --> 00:36:31,222
Fighting those machines
is impossible.

370
00:36:31,693 --> 00:36:33,437
We keep our heads down,
they ignore us.

371
00:36:33,472 --> 00:36:35,678
You keep your heads down
and they'll come for you eventually.

372
00:36:35,713 --> 00:36:37,227
We help you
and maybe they will.

373
00:36:38,063 --> 00:36:39,541
These people
aren't gonna help you.

374
00:36:40,236 --> 00:36:40,873
Let's go.

375
00:36:40,873 --> 00:36:42,214
You're not going
anywhere.

376
00:36:43,020 --> 00:36:45,272
Not until this one
gets something to eat.

377
00:36:55,792 --> 00:36:56,948
Bring me a basket.

378
00:36:59,268 --> 00:37:00,460
Here you go.

379
00:37:02,992 --> 00:37:05,671
Come on, help yourself!
Eat up.

380
00:37:14,832 --> 00:37:16,416
Are you alright, son?

381
00:37:18,731 --> 00:37:19,804
It's our food.

382
00:37:20,524 --> 00:37:21,621
Our fuel.

383
00:37:22,904 --> 00:37:24,531
It's not your choice
to make!

384
00:37:58,145 --> 00:37:59,607
- Are you okay?
- What?

385
00:37:59,646 --> 00:38:00,915
Are you okay?

386
00:38:01,655 --> 00:38:03,591
Star, Star!

387
00:38:04,288 --> 00:38:06,144
Damn!
You brought them here!

388
00:38:06,145 --> 00:38:07,120
You brought them here.

389
00:38:09,193 --> 00:38:10,040
Hey!

390
00:38:12,518 --> 00:38:13,894
- Stop, stop!
- Come on, wait.

391
00:38:14,956 --> 00:38:17,793
- Hey!
- Go! Go get 'em, go!

392
00:38:30,888 --> 00:38:32,646
- Head for the tunnels!
- Truck!

393
00:38:46,247 --> 00:38:47,548
Marcus, Marcus!

394
00:38:50,507 --> 00:38:51,687
We can't
just run for it.

395
00:39:02,823 --> 00:39:03,942
Run!

396
00:39:40,635 --> 00:39:41,598
Shoot it!

397
00:39:46,874 --> 00:39:47,980
Go, go, go!

398
00:39:54,545 --> 00:39:55,583
It didn't work!

399
00:39:57,225 --> 00:39:58,070
Shit!

400
00:40:31,256 --> 00:40:32,180
Hell, yeah!

401
00:40:50,439 --> 00:40:51,606
Mototerminators!

402
00:41:04,465 --> 00:41:05,802
Shoot that
son of a bitch!

403
00:41:23,871 --> 00:41:25,247
Marcus,
turn right up here.

404
00:41:38,111 --> 00:41:38,858
Hold on!

405
00:41:49,440 --> 00:41:50,544
Where is the other one?

406
00:42:06,845 --> 00:42:07,894
Get up here!

407
00:42:14,940 --> 00:42:15,951
Come on!

408
00:42:16,924 --> 00:42:18,166
Star,
give me the gun.

409
00:42:19,307 --> 00:42:20,001
I got it.

410
00:42:22,870 --> 00:42:23,738
Yeah!

411
00:42:34,154 --> 00:42:35,074
Hang on!

412
00:42:43,220 --> 00:42:45,621
- Drop the ball!
- Uh, alright.

413
00:43:25,170 --> 00:43:26,479
Star, go!

414
00:43:33,932 --> 00:43:35,853
- Star!
- No!

415
00:44:16,016 --> 00:44:16,980
Kyle!

416
00:44:17,521 --> 00:44:17,944
Marcus!

417
00:44:17,970 --> 00:44:18,789
Get back!

418
00:44:24,280 --> 00:44:26,957
Marcus! Marcus!

419
00:44:31,712 --> 00:44:33,099
<i>I got my eyes on
two targets.</i>

420
00:44:33,134 --> 00:44:35,456
<i>We've got two bogeys
at 270º.</i>

421
00:44:36,103 --> 00:44:37,373
They've never come
this deep before.

422
00:44:37,408 --> 00:44:38,405
They're looking
for something.

423
00:44:45,496 --> 00:44:46,709
<i>H.K. is down.</i>

424
00:45:02,400 --> 00:45:04,283
<i>We've got an H.K.
porching our six.</i>

425
00:45:04,445 --> 00:45:06,482
<i>Come over by.
Breaking off.</i>

426
00:45:13,461 --> 00:45:15,416
Evasive maneuvers
now!

427
00:45:20,676 --> 00:45:23,033
<i>Taking fire. I'm hit.
Portside damage.</i>

428
00:45:29,121 --> 00:45:30,812
It's got a lock on you.
Break off.

429
00:45:33,662 --> 00:45:35,515
Eject, Williams, eject!

430
00:45:35,550 --> 00:45:36,597
<i>Punching out.</i>

431
00:45:54,656 --> 00:45:57,052
There's your transport,
headed northwest,

432
00:45:58,356 --> 00:46:01,106
bearing 2-8-9
towards San Francisco.

433
00:46:02,998 --> 00:46:04,526
First,
test the signal...

434
00:46:05,916 --> 00:46:07,177
and pray it works.

435
00:47:04,573 --> 00:47:05,268
You okay?

436
00:47:06,230 --> 00:47:08,967
Get my knife.
It's in my left boot.

437
00:47:16,680 --> 00:47:17,488
What's your name?

438
00:47:18,485 --> 00:47:19,539
Blair Williams.

439
00:47:22,208 --> 00:47:23,012
What's yours?

440
00:47:27,702 --> 00:47:28,881
Name's Marcus.

441
00:47:30,049 --> 00:47:31,819
You can let me down now,
Marcus.

442
00:47:40,511 --> 00:47:43,393
- That thing, where'd it go?
- The transport?

443
00:47:43,985 --> 00:47:44,956
Skynet.

444
00:47:45,629 --> 00:47:46,616
Where the hell
are you going?

445
00:47:47,077 --> 00:47:47,804
After it.

446
00:47:48,756 --> 00:47:50,233
Hate to break it
to you but...

447
00:47:50,865 --> 00:47:52,389
If you've got friends
on that thing...

448
00:47:52,612 --> 00:47:53,733
They're good as dead.

449
00:47:54,222 --> 00:47:56,443
The same is you
if you keep walking in that direction.

450
00:47:56,642 --> 00:47:58,711
They've only been dead a while
and I am getting used to it.

451
00:47:59,613 --> 00:48:01,147
Why don't you come with me
to my base?

452
00:48:01,815 --> 00:48:03,104
Connor might know why.

453
00:48:07,492 --> 00:48:09,406
Listen, if you've got a problem
with the machines,

454
00:48:09,789 --> 00:48:11,508
he's definitely the guy
you wanna talk to.

455
00:48:14,249 --> 00:48:16,734
- How far is your base?
- It should be 1 or 2 days hike.

456
00:48:18,212 --> 00:48:19,175
And it's that way.

457
00:48:44,424 --> 00:48:46,465
What are you saying?
Speak English!

458
00:48:49,187 --> 00:48:50,614
I was telling him...

459
00:48:50,894 --> 00:48:53,935
It is not true,
the part the machines killing us.

460
00:48:54,255 --> 00:48:57,169
They're gonna kill us.
They're gonna kill everyone.

461
00:48:57,180 --> 00:48:58,498
We are
in a cattle cart,

462
00:48:58,503 --> 00:48:59,920
on our way
to the slaughterhouse.

463
00:48:59,955 --> 00:49:02,838
Calm down.
You're not helping.

464
00:49:03,468 --> 00:49:06,392
The most important thing
that we can do right now

465
00:49:06,427 --> 00:49:07,761
is stay alive.

466
00:49:08,227 --> 00:49:10,115
In here
and in here.

467
00:49:11,063 --> 00:49:14,110
Alright?
Just stay alive.

468
00:49:30,063 --> 00:49:30,862
Over there.

469
00:49:38,260 --> 00:49:39,675
Find something
that can burn.

470
00:49:40,290 --> 00:49:41,625
We'll be
at my base tomorrow.

471
00:49:45,189 --> 00:49:45,833
Are you hurt?

472
00:49:48,578 --> 00:49:49,492
I'm fine.

473
00:50:09,180 --> 00:50:10,636
What you got there?

474
00:50:14,447 --> 00:50:15,695
Just some antibiotics.

475
00:50:16,475 --> 00:50:18,666
Antibiotics are hard
to come by these days.

476
00:50:19,630 --> 00:50:21,247
Listen,
I don't have much, but...

477
00:50:21,282 --> 00:50:22,500
you're welcome
to whatever you need.

478
00:50:23,654 --> 00:50:25,090
We've been watching you.

479
00:50:27,169 --> 00:50:28,139
Looking for this?

480
00:50:30,367 --> 00:50:33,066
Come on, guys.
Machines are the enemy.

481
00:50:33,395 --> 00:50:35,492
- We're on the same side.
- No, no.

482
00:50:36,121 --> 00:50:38,170
See, I've got a couple of friends
on my side.

483
00:50:38,656 --> 00:50:40,392
Maybe they can
carry you home...

484
00:50:41,048 --> 00:50:42,256
when I'm done with you.

485
00:50:44,846 --> 00:50:46,576
You might want
a chamber around.

486
00:51:27,827 --> 00:51:29,530
Kill me,
you ain't gonna win this war.

487
00:51:34,712 --> 00:51:36,773
Ow! Oh, God!

488
00:52:22,566 --> 00:52:24,124
I'm a little cold.

489
00:52:33,501 --> 00:52:34,593
Relax.

490
00:52:38,060 --> 00:52:39,770
I just want
some body heat.

491
00:52:46,535 --> 00:52:48,143
You have
a strong heart.

492
00:52:50,852 --> 00:52:52,619
God,
I love that sound.

493
00:52:59,898 --> 00:53:00,907
Thank you...

494
00:53:01,938 --> 00:53:03,508
for saving me
back there.

495
00:53:05,067 --> 00:53:07,346
I don't meet a lot
of good guys these days.

496
00:53:09,629 --> 00:53:10,864
I'm not
a good guy.

497
00:53:17,848 --> 00:53:19,052
You are.

498
00:53:20,459 --> 00:53:22,046
You just
don't know it, yet.

499
00:53:31,580 --> 00:53:33,853
Do you think people
deserve a second chance?

500
00:53:37,816 --> 00:53:38,670
Yeah.

501
00:53:39,500 --> 00:53:40,165
I do.

502
00:53:44,191 --> 00:53:45,076
This is it.

503
00:53:45,332 --> 00:53:47,037
Skynet's Valley of Death.

504
00:53:47,072 --> 00:53:48,983
We've never been
this deep before.

505
00:53:49,018 --> 00:53:50,311
We've got to be sure
this thing works

506
00:53:50,346 --> 00:53:51,329
in their territory.

507
00:53:52,061 --> 00:53:53,311
On the bigger machines.

508
00:54:04,887 --> 00:54:05,899
That will bring them in.

509
00:54:23,545 --> 00:54:25,049
H.K.
They're coming.

510
00:54:47,157 --> 00:54:47,931
Turn it up!

511
00:55:10,997 --> 00:55:13,428
It works, man.
The signal works.

512
00:55:13,463 --> 00:55:14,475
It's beautiful!

513
00:55:26,259 --> 00:55:29,091
<i>- Commander Ashdown.
- Connor, tell me it works.</i>

514
00:55:29,393 --> 00:55:30,159
It works.

515
00:55:30,194 --> 00:55:32,275
That is affirmative.
The signal works.

516
00:55:32,726 --> 00:55:33,407
Good.

517
00:55:33,817 --> 00:55:36,631
The attack commences tomorrow
at 0400, worldwide.

518
00:55:36,666 --> 00:55:39,741
<i>Your unit will be in support
of a bombing in Skynet's central.</i>

519
00:55:40,107 --> 00:55:42,437
What is the extraction plan
for the prisoners?

520
00:55:42,472 --> 00:55:43,272
<i>Extraction plan?</i>

521
00:55:43,307 --> 00:55:44,951
<i>There is
no extraction plan.</i>

522
00:55:44,986 --> 00:55:46,203
We're gonna level
the place.

523
00:55:47,112 --> 00:55:49,104
Negative!
I told you.

524
00:55:49,616 --> 00:55:52,676
Skynet Central
is filled with human prisoners.

525
00:55:54,290 --> 00:55:56,986
This is war, Connor.
Leadership has its cost.

526
00:55:57,021 --> 00:55:58,383
You, above all,
should know that.

527
00:56:01,525 --> 00:56:02,721
Ashdown, come in.

528
00:56:03,912 --> 00:56:04,949
Ashdown, Connor.

529
00:56:05,795 --> 00:56:07,920
Ashdown, Con...
Damn him!

530
00:56:21,921 --> 00:56:25,119
Star! Get back!
Get back!

531
00:56:31,453 --> 00:56:33,376
You have
to calm down, now.

532
00:56:49,448 --> 00:56:51,533
I gotta get
out of here!

533
00:57:07,199 --> 00:57:07,897
Blair.

534
00:57:08,476 --> 00:57:09,203
What?

535
00:57:12,878 --> 00:57:15,554
This is us.
The mines are magnetic.

536
00:57:16,212 --> 00:57:17,761
If we head due west
at this point of entry,

537
00:57:17,796 --> 00:57:18,614
we're good.

538
00:57:21,737 --> 00:57:22,614
I'll go first.

539
00:57:52,163 --> 00:57:54,311
Let's go, Marcus.
I'm starving.

540
00:58:03,638 --> 00:58:05,104
<i>For thou art with me,</i>

541
00:58:05,876 --> 00:58:08,235
<i>thy rod and my staff,</i>

542
00:58:08,470 --> 00:58:09,982
- they comfort me.
- Father.

543
00:58:12,886 --> 00:58:15,422
<i>This is the beginning</i>

544
00:58:15,457 --> 00:58:17,470
of something
wonderful.

545
00:58:19,516 --> 00:58:21,652
- The son of a bitch is here.
- What do we've got here?

546
00:58:21,687 --> 00:58:23,062
He stepped
on a landmine.

547
00:58:23,197 --> 00:58:24,868
Start a large four IV.

548
00:58:25,348 --> 00:58:26,143
Keep it open.

549
00:58:26,189 --> 00:58:27,393
- I'm okay.
- Patient needs more morphine.

550
00:58:27,428 --> 00:58:29,262
- What's his name?
- Marcus.

551
00:58:31,966 --> 00:58:33,467
He's got
a prosthetic limb?

552
00:58:33,879 --> 00:58:34,641
What?

553
00:58:35,637 --> 00:58:37,128
Okay,
pulse is dead.

554
00:58:37,163 --> 00:58:38,427
Let's see
what we've got here.

555
00:58:44,696 --> 00:58:45,656
Barnes?

556
00:58:51,713 --> 00:58:53,692
<i>The Devil's hands
have been busy.</i>

557
00:58:56,456 --> 00:58:59,329
- What is it?
- It's real flesh and blood.

558
00:58:59,800 --> 00:59:01,668
Though it seems
to heal his off quickly.

559
00:59:02,405 --> 00:59:06,420
The heart is human,
but very powerful.

560
00:59:06,842 --> 00:59:09,202
The brain too,
but with a chip interface.

561
00:59:09,295 --> 00:59:12,200
- He done enough?
- It has a hybrid nervous system.

562
00:59:12,655 --> 00:59:14,570
One human cortex.

563
00:59:15,083 --> 00:59:17,217
- One machine.
- What the hell would have they done?

564
00:59:18,775 --> 00:59:19,905
Who built you?

565
00:59:21,454 --> 00:59:24,618
My name is
Marcus Wright.

566
00:59:25,844 --> 00:59:27,222
You think
you're human?

567
00:59:28,212 --> 00:59:29,256
I am human.

568
00:59:55,484 --> 00:59:57,542
No!

569
00:59:58,833 --> 01:00:01,370
No! God!

570
01:00:04,160 --> 01:00:05,725
Where were you
manufactured?

571
01:00:06,906 --> 01:00:07,867
I was born...

572
01:00:09,492 --> 01:00:12,052
August 22nd, 1975.

573
01:00:23,917 --> 01:00:24,970
I know you.

574
01:00:26,414 --> 01:00:28,565
I heard your voice
on the radio.

575
01:00:30,621 --> 01:00:32,731
- You're John Connor.
- Of course you know me.

576
01:00:34,497 --> 01:00:36,157
You were sent here
to kill me.

577
01:00:37,344 --> 01:00:38,650
Kill the leadership.

578
01:00:39,560 --> 01:00:41,400
I don't know
what you're talking about.

579
01:00:41,497 --> 01:00:42,486
Then why are you here?

580
01:00:42,645 --> 01:00:44,977
Blair said you could help me
find who I'm looking for.

581
01:00:49,170 --> 01:00:50,357
Now let me down.

582
01:00:51,107 --> 01:00:52,649
If I let you down...

583
01:00:53,961 --> 01:00:55,579
you'll kill everyone
in this room.

584
01:00:56,413 --> 01:00:57,751
Just you, Connor.

585
01:00:58,752 --> 01:01:00,355
'Cause I ain't
give a shit about you.

586
01:01:01,138 --> 01:01:03,450
I didn't even know your name
until two days ago.

587
01:01:03,485 --> 01:01:04,131
No?

588
01:01:08,718 --> 01:01:09,569
You and me...

589
01:01:11,243 --> 01:01:12,495
We've been at war,

590
01:01:13,602 --> 01:01:15,709
since before
either of us even existed.

591
01:01:17,704 --> 01:01:20,919
You tried killing my mother,
Sarah Connor.

592
01:01:22,160 --> 01:01:24,991
You killed my father,
Kyle Reese.

593
01:01:26,105 --> 01:01:28,427
You will not
kill me.

594
01:01:30,226 --> 01:01:35,135
Kyle Reese is on a Transporter,
heading for Skynet.

595
01:01:36,436 --> 01:01:38,231
If I wanted
to kill him,

596
01:01:39,481 --> 01:01:40,993
I would have done him
in L.A.

597
01:01:47,803 --> 01:01:49,078
Where did you
find that thing?

598
01:01:49,399 --> 01:01:52,477
You sent Mihradi and me
to provide cover for some civilians.

599
01:01:52,512 --> 01:01:53,449
He was
one of them.

600
01:01:54,188 --> 01:01:55,421
Was there
a teenage boy?

601
01:01:56,082 --> 01:01:57,508
I honestly don't know.

602
01:01:57,543 --> 01:01:58,907
They were taking him
to a Transport.

603
01:01:58,942 --> 01:02:02,206
<i>- He was the only one left.
- Not he, Blair. It.</i>

604
01:02:02,790 --> 01:02:04,689
<i>"It was the only one left."
Don't be naïve.</i>

605
01:02:05,489 --> 01:02:06,976
It saved my life.

606
01:02:10,782 --> 01:02:12,282
Kate, what's gonna
happen to him?

607
01:02:13,849 --> 01:02:14,970
Disassembled.

608
01:02:16,024 --> 01:02:17,129
You mean killed.

609
01:02:17,568 --> 01:02:19,742
It may have information
on Skynet.

610
01:02:21,789 --> 01:02:23,615
I know
he's not the enemy.

611
01:02:24,038 --> 01:02:25,555
I've been shot at
by the enemy.

612
01:02:25,590 --> 01:02:26,556
That's not him.

613
01:02:26,591 --> 01:02:29,621
That machine saved you
only to gain access

614
01:02:29,656 --> 01:02:30,809
to kill all of us.

615
01:03:11,191 --> 01:03:13,088
We're gonna be okay.
Don't worry.

616
01:03:30,720 --> 01:03:31,898
For my brother.

617
01:03:43,049 --> 01:03:45,797
No!

618
01:03:51,563 --> 01:03:52,789
Connor wants
to see you.

619
01:03:53,896 --> 01:03:54,744
What for?

620
01:03:55,620 --> 01:03:57,454
Like he's going to tell me,
Barnes.

621
01:04:00,404 --> 01:04:01,188
Let me see that.

622
01:04:08,773 --> 01:04:10,423
You want me to tell Connor
you're not coming?

623
01:04:10,458 --> 01:04:11,238
No.

624
01:04:16,454 --> 01:04:17,359
Watch him.

625
01:04:45,510 --> 01:04:47,696
<i>I told you everything
I know, John.</i>

626
01:04:48,201 --> 01:04:51,199
<i>Skynet is ruthless
and unpredictable.</i>

627
01:04:51,234 --> 01:04:54,537
<i>They will use the best part of you
against yourself,</i>

628
01:04:55,091 --> 01:04:58,228
<i>and they will have methods
I can't imagine or predict.</i>

629
01:04:58,446 --> 01:05:00,418
<i>That I can't
help you with.</i>

630
01:05:01,037 --> 01:05:02,536
<i>And when
you're unsure,</i>

631
01:05:03,379 --> 01:05:05,792
<i>which just always
follow your heart, John.</i>

632
01:05:06,546 --> 01:05:08,975
<i>I love you.
Goodbye.</i>

633
01:05:11,448 --> 01:05:13,906
There's nothing on the tapes
about machines with organs.

634
01:05:14,223 --> 01:05:15,585
That thing in there...

635
01:05:18,845 --> 01:05:20,334
I thought I knew
our enemy.

636
01:05:21,114 --> 01:05:22,237
But that thing...

637
01:05:23,094 --> 01:05:24,721
That makes me feel like
I know nothing.

638
01:05:26,944 --> 01:05:29,602
I looked in its eyes,
and it believes,

639
01:05:30,032 --> 01:05:32,538
absolutely believes,
that it is human.

640
01:05:32,933 --> 01:05:36,362
<i>It believes everything
that it says,</i>

641
01:05:36,397 --> 01:05:40,563
and it is telling me
that Kyle Reese is in Skynet.

642
01:05:42,038 --> 01:05:43,338
If that is true...

643
01:05:43,911 --> 01:05:47,311
The Command is about
to bomb my father

644
01:05:47,508 --> 01:05:51,320
and the rest of those prisoners
and I cannot stop them.

645
01:05:58,719 --> 01:05:59,672
Thank you.

646
01:06:01,456 --> 01:06:02,261
Come in!

647
01:06:05,103 --> 01:06:07,294
Wassup?
Blair says you needed me.

648
01:06:28,774 --> 01:06:29,291
Get in!

649
01:06:31,510 --> 01:06:32,315
Kill them!

650
01:06:40,209 --> 01:06:42,419
Barnes!
What about Blair?

651
01:06:42,934 --> 01:06:44,483
She made her choice.

652
01:06:44,518 --> 01:06:45,338
Get down!

653
01:06:58,188 --> 01:06:59,000
Let's move.

654
01:07:11,718 --> 01:07:14,158
- Put some light out there!
- We're back in the minefield.

655
01:07:14,653 --> 01:07:15,533
I have a plan.

656
01:07:40,032 --> 01:07:42,096
- Blair, you okay?
- Yeah, I'm okay!

657
01:07:42,131 --> 01:07:44,291
- Get your team back!
- There they are!

658
01:07:45,224 --> 01:07:46,397
Run! God--

659
01:07:57,823 --> 01:07:58,752
Now what?

660
01:07:59,969 --> 01:08:01,502
M-My plan stopped
at the jeep.

661
01:08:01,984 --> 01:08:02,817
Okay.

662
01:08:04,082 --> 01:08:05,440
Do you have
the shot?

663
01:08:13,045 --> 01:08:16,007
I'll draw the fire.
You take out the light.

664
01:08:24,910 --> 01:08:26,349
I got a target!

665
01:08:29,497 --> 01:08:30,206
Behind the wall.

666
01:08:30,774 --> 01:08:31,789
- Don't move.
- Go!

667
01:08:32,307 --> 01:08:33,305
Down!

668
01:08:33,340 --> 01:08:34,377
Keep your head down!

669
01:08:34,412 --> 01:08:37,185
Keep your head down!
Go, go, go, go!

670
01:08:45,217 --> 01:08:46,033
Come on!

671
01:08:52,568 --> 01:08:55,110
- You alright?
- Let's get you out of here.

672
01:09:01,332 --> 01:09:02,203
There they are!

673
01:09:20,925 --> 01:09:23,002
On the ground!
Stay on the ground!

674
01:09:23,037 --> 01:09:24,095
<i>Report 47.</i>

675
01:09:25,985 --> 01:09:27,134
<i>Coming straight down.
I'm going in.</i>

676
01:09:27,169 --> 01:09:29,143
- Do not move!
- Keep your eye on them.

677
01:09:30,028 --> 01:09:30,803
Who's there?

678
01:10:13,194 --> 01:10:16,651
<i>Alligator, this is Scarface 5-1,
we have eyes on the machine.</i>

679
01:10:16,686 --> 01:10:17,713
<i>Contact--</i>

680
01:10:32,250 --> 01:10:33,429
Take my gun!

681
01:11:07,164 --> 01:11:08,127
<i>Check the river.</i>

682
01:11:24,359 --> 01:11:25,202
You see him?

683
01:11:29,800 --> 01:11:30,597
Move!

684
01:11:39,400 --> 01:11:40,185
God!

685
01:11:52,193 --> 01:11:53,639
I'm going down!

686
01:12:02,919 --> 01:12:03,893
Fall!

687
01:12:05,838 --> 01:12:08,010
Give me your hand!
Give me your hand!

688
01:12:57,403 --> 01:12:59,165
They know what you are,
even if you don't.

689
01:12:59,200 --> 01:13:00,056
Enough!

690
01:13:01,246 --> 01:13:02,593
That gun ain't
gonna stop shit!

691
01:13:02,625 --> 01:13:03,866
Nobody shot you
in the heart,

692
01:13:03,901 --> 01:13:05,838
and I see that thing
beating a mile a minute.

693
01:13:05,873 --> 01:13:06,891
Kyle Reese...

694
01:13:08,232 --> 01:13:10,205
He's in Skynet.
You do that, he's dead.

695
01:13:11,498 --> 01:13:12,750
I can get you in.

696
01:13:14,853 --> 01:13:15,570
How?

697
01:13:22,551 --> 01:13:23,617
Look at me.

698
01:13:25,924 --> 01:13:27,626
That's why
I don't trust you.

699
01:13:30,101 --> 01:13:31,783
I'm your only hope
you have.

700
01:13:35,962 --> 01:13:38,071
I need to find
who did this to me.

701
01:13:40,382 --> 01:13:41,399
So do you.

702
01:13:42,072 --> 01:13:43,585
Connor!

703
01:13:50,652 --> 01:13:51,737
Make your choice.

704
01:13:53,939 --> 01:13:54,904
You kept being...

705
01:13:58,190 --> 01:14:01,881
You tell me
where I can find Kyle Reese.

706
01:14:04,203 --> 01:14:07,067
- Yeah?
- I will.

707
01:14:13,650 --> 01:14:14,893
Contact me on that.

708
01:14:16,052 --> 01:14:17,434
Let me know
he's still alive.

709
01:14:23,838 --> 01:14:24,989
What are you?

710
01:14:26,076 --> 01:14:26,936
I don't know.

711
01:14:34,596 --> 01:14:35,871
Hey,
he's over here.

712
01:14:35,906 --> 01:14:36,894
Where is he heading?

713
01:14:39,504 --> 01:14:40,360
You alright?

714
01:14:42,234 --> 01:14:43,319
Any sign of him?

715
01:14:45,111 --> 01:14:45,871
He's gone.

716
01:14:54,337 --> 01:14:55,248
What'd you do?

717
01:14:57,217 --> 01:15:00,382
I saw a man,
not a machine.

718
01:15:09,101 --> 01:15:10,162
How's your leg?

719
01:15:11,026 --> 01:15:12,038
I'll live.

720
01:15:12,786 --> 01:15:13,590
Let me go!

721
01:15:23,467 --> 01:15:24,104
Connor.

722
01:15:25,006 --> 01:15:25,723
Command for you.

723
01:15:27,527 --> 01:15:28,520
This is Connor.

724
01:15:28,632 --> 01:15:30,108
Connor,
are your men ready?

725
01:15:30,327 --> 01:15:32,651
<i>Negative.
Nobody is ready.</i>

726
01:15:32,686 --> 01:15:34,244
We are not,
you are not.

727
01:15:34,279 --> 01:15:37,445
We must abort the attack.
The game has changed.

728
01:15:37,480 --> 01:15:38,772
What are you talking about?

729
01:15:38,807 --> 01:15:40,914
All our elements
are past the release points.

730
01:15:40,949 --> 01:15:42,811
They are in
assault position.

731
01:15:42,846 --> 01:15:46,047
Then delay the attack.
At least, delay the attack.

732
01:15:46,082 --> 01:15:47,839
I have a chance
to infiltrate Skynet

733
01:15:47,874 --> 01:15:49,317
and rescue
those prisoners.

734
01:15:49,352 --> 01:15:50,511
Give me
that opportunity.

735
01:15:50,546 --> 01:15:51,804
No, absolutely not.

736
01:15:52,031 --> 01:15:54,117
This is not the time
for a rescue mission.

737
01:15:54,152 --> 01:15:57,040
What you ask for,
will undermine the whole operation.

738
01:15:57,075 --> 01:15:59,465
Skynet has Kyle Reese.

739
01:16:00,122 --> 01:16:01,361
And that is his fate.

740
01:16:01,396 --> 01:16:02,630
<i>No, it's our fate.</i>

741
01:16:02,665 --> 01:16:05,675
I have to save him.
He is the key.

742
01:16:05,710 --> 01:16:08,124
The key to the future,
to the past.

743
01:16:08,262 --> 01:16:11,018
Without him,
we lose everything.

744
01:16:11,053 --> 01:16:12,554
No!
You stay the course!

745
01:16:12,808 --> 01:16:15,686
If we stay the course,
we are dead!

746
01:16:15,980 --> 01:16:17,654
We are all dead!

747
01:16:18,862 --> 01:16:20,423
<i>As of this moment,
soldier,</i>

748
01:16:20,458 --> 01:16:22,226
you are relieved
to your command.

749
01:16:22,261 --> 01:16:25,273
You are no longer
a part of this Resistance.

750
01:16:32,895 --> 01:16:34,869
I didn't catch
that last statement.

751
01:16:35,580 --> 01:16:36,628
Neither did I.

752
01:16:40,511 --> 01:16:41,387
This is John Connor.

753
01:16:41,555 --> 01:16:42,814
If you're listening
to this,

754
01:16:42,944 --> 01:16:44,627
you are
the Resistance.

755
01:16:45,852 --> 01:16:47,086
<i>Listen carefully.</i>

756
01:16:47,290 --> 01:16:48,638
<i>If we attack tonight,</i>

757
01:16:49,365 --> 01:16:51,331
<i>our humanity is lost.</i>

758
01:16:52,874 --> 01:16:54,873
Command wants us
to fight like machines,

759
01:16:54,909 --> 01:16:57,633
they want us to make
cold, calculated decisions.

760
01:16:58,257 --> 01:17:00,002
But we are not
machines.

761
01:17:00,552 --> 01:17:03,329
And if we behave like them,
then what is the point...

762
01:17:03,559 --> 01:17:04,478
in winning?

763
01:17:06,110 --> 01:17:10,068
<i>Command is going to ask you
to attack Skynet.</i>

764
01:17:10,946 --> 01:17:12,658
<i>I am asking you
not to.</i>

765
01:17:16,055 --> 01:17:20,289
If even one bomb
drops on Skynet before sunrise,

766
01:17:20,518 --> 01:17:23,388
our future will be lost.

767
01:17:24,133 --> 01:17:26,429
<i>So, please.
Stand down.</i>

768
01:17:26,841 --> 01:17:27,990
<i>Give me the time</i>

769
01:17:28,498 --> 01:17:30,963
<i>to protect our future,
that all of us,</i>

770
01:17:31,640 --> 01:17:33,164
<i>are fighting for.</i>

771
01:17:36,224 --> 01:17:37,342
This is
John Connor.

772
01:17:55,244 --> 01:17:55,936
Thank you.

773
01:18:01,900 --> 01:18:04,606
What should I tell your men
when they find out you're gone?

774
01:18:09,265 --> 01:18:10,176
I'll be back.

775
01:18:28,127 --> 01:18:34,305
[Song: You Could Be Mine
Band: Guns N' Roses]

776
01:20:03,975 --> 01:20:05,469
I'm coming for you.

777
01:20:51,072 --> 01:20:52,633
Come on, Marcus.

778
01:22:04,333 --> 01:22:05,165
Okay.

779
01:23:43,227 --> 01:23:45,664
Signal broadcasted
with full thrift, sir.

780
01:23:45,699 --> 01:23:46,742
Good.

781
01:23:47,209 --> 01:23:48,854
Commence
bombing of Skynet.

782
01:23:48,889 --> 01:23:50,466
We have a green light
for the attack.

783
01:23:51,037 --> 01:23:52,234
<i>This is Bakersfield.</i>

784
01:23:52,269 --> 01:23:54,113
<i>That's a no-go
on your last. Out.</i>

785
01:23:53,848 --> 01:23:54,308
<i>Eugene.</i>

786
01:23:54,332 --> 01:23:55,041
<i>Standing down.</i>

787
01:23:55,095 --> 01:23:56,764
<i>This is Reno.
Negative on your last.</i>

788
01:23:56,799 --> 01:24:00,023
Eugene, Reno, Bakersfield,
they're all standing down.

789
01:24:00,058 --> 01:24:02,990
They will not attack,
unless Connor gives the order.

790
01:24:31,000 --> 01:24:32,045
Kyle Reese?

791
01:24:32,222 --> 01:24:34,236
Go!
Get to your transport!

792
01:24:34,479 --> 01:24:35,219
Go!

793
01:24:35,254 --> 01:24:37,016
Is Kyle Reese here?

794
01:24:57,125 --> 01:25:00,675
<i>Welcome home, Marcus.
We knew you'd be back.</i>

795
01:25:01,410 --> 01:25:03,971
<i>After all,
it was programmed in you.</i>

796
01:25:05,238 --> 01:25:09,512
<i>Oh, and you executed
that programming beautifully.</i>

797
01:25:10,198 --> 01:25:11,077
What am I?

798
01:25:11,674 --> 01:25:13,570
You are
an Infiltration Prototype.

799
01:25:13,963 --> 01:25:15,386
The only
one of your kind.

800
01:25:16,070 --> 01:25:17,279
We resurrected you.

801
01:25:17,822 --> 01:25:21,083
<i>Advanced CyberDyne's work...
amended it.</i>

802
01:25:21,118 --> 01:25:22,148
You're dead.

803
01:25:22,700 --> 01:25:24,571
<i>Calculations confirmed
the Serena code</i>

804
01:25:24,606 --> 01:25:26,791
<i>on this face
isn't easiest for you to process.</i>

805
01:25:27,686 --> 01:25:29,493
<i>It can be others
if you wish.</i>

806
01:25:32,198 --> 01:25:33,201
<i>Marcus...</i>

807
01:25:33,835 --> 01:25:36,865
<i>What else could you be...
if not machine?</i>

808
01:25:37,850 --> 01:25:38,666
A man.

809
01:25:39,365 --> 01:25:41,819
<i>The human condition
no longer applies to you.</i>

810
01:25:42,492 --> 01:25:44,222
<i>Accept what you
already know...</i>

811
01:25:44,941 --> 01:25:47,653
<i>That you were made
to serve a purpose.</i>

812
01:25:48,369 --> 01:25:51,382
<i>To achieve what no another machine
has achieved before.</i>

813
01:25:53,143 --> 01:25:55,576
<i>To infiltrate,
find a target,</i>

814
01:25:56,160 --> 01:25:58,590
<i>and then bring that target
back home to us.</i>

815
01:26:01,807 --> 01:26:05,016
<i>We've been at war since before
either of us even existed.</i>

816
01:26:06,025 --> 01:26:09,136
<i>You tried killing my mother,
Sarah Connor.</i>

817
01:26:09,803 --> 01:26:10,589
<i>You kept being...</i>

818
01:26:12,005 --> 01:26:14,615
<i>You tell me
where I can find Kyle Reese.</i>

819
01:26:15,107 --> 01:26:17,204
<i>Yeah, I will.</i>

820
01:26:20,669 --> 01:26:22,875
Kyle Reese!
Kyle Reese!

821
01:26:22,910 --> 01:26:24,357
Move! Move!

822
01:26:25,187 --> 01:26:26,123
Kyle Reese!

823
01:26:27,457 --> 01:26:28,944
Get to your transport.

824
01:26:29,556 --> 01:26:30,405
Kyle Reese!

825
01:26:37,479 --> 01:26:39,265
You, move!

826
01:26:40,127 --> 01:26:41,740
<i>In times of desperation,</i>

827
01:26:41,775 --> 01:26:44,012
<i>people will believe
what they want to believe.</i>

828
01:26:44,360 --> 01:26:48,487
<i>And so, we gave them
what they wanted to believe.</i>

829
01:26:48,543 --> 01:26:50,661
<i>A trick,
in the form of a signal,</i>

830
01:26:50,696 --> 01:26:52,763
<i>the Resistance thought
would win the war.</i>

831
01:26:52,798 --> 01:26:55,108
<i>And they were right,
it will end this war.</i>

832
01:26:55,436 --> 01:26:58,716
<i>Except that it is the Resistance
that will be terminated,</i>

833
01:26:59,474 --> 01:27:00,683
<i>not Skynet.</i>

834
01:27:07,822 --> 01:27:10,647
Get the attack through
Skynet's Central back online.

835
01:27:10,741 --> 01:27:13,557
I want our aircraft in the sky,
immediately!

836
01:27:13,805 --> 01:27:16,874
Sir, sir, we got a bogey
with a very large radar signature,

837
01:27:16,909 --> 01:27:18,182
closing in
on our position.

838
01:27:29,708 --> 01:27:30,616
Losenko?

839
01:27:36,292 --> 01:27:38,376
We have destroyed
ourselves.

840
01:27:39,253 --> 01:27:41,174
Skynet tracked
our signal.

841
01:27:41,209 --> 01:27:42,795
We led them
straight to us.

842
01:27:56,160 --> 01:27:58,275
<i>Our best machines have failed,
time and again,</i>

843
01:27:58,310 --> 01:27:59,509
<i>to complete a mission.</i>

844
01:28:00,120 --> 01:28:01,355
<i>Something was missing.</i>

845
01:28:01,607 --> 01:28:04,037
<i>We had to think,
radically.</i>

846
01:28:04,483 --> 01:28:05,919
<i>And so we made you.</i>

847
01:28:06,254 --> 01:28:09,311
<i>We created the perfect
infiltration machine.</i>

848
01:28:10,476 --> 01:28:11,730
<i>You, Marcus.</i>

849
01:28:12,350 --> 01:28:15,876
<i>You did what Skynet
has failed to do for so many years.</i>

850
01:28:16,831 --> 01:28:18,519
<i>You killed John Connor.</i>

851
01:29:19,369 --> 01:29:20,881
Kyle!

852
01:29:21,712 --> 01:29:22,698
Hey!

853
01:29:32,712 --> 01:29:34,016
<i>Don't fight, Marcus.</i>

854
01:29:35,093 --> 01:29:36,888
<i>Remember
what you are.</i>

855
01:29:37,985 --> 01:29:39,351
I know what I am.

856
01:29:52,918 --> 01:29:54,216
I'm better this way.

857
01:29:54,457 --> 01:29:56,807
<i>You will not be given
a second chance.</i>

858
01:29:57,567 --> 01:29:59,607
<i>You cannot save
John Connor.</i>

859
01:30:00,498 --> 01:30:01,438
Watch me.

860
01:30:31,357 --> 01:30:33,085
We got a message
from Connor!

861
01:30:33,548 --> 01:30:35,426
He's in Skynet.
Needs air support.

862
01:30:37,988 --> 01:30:40,283
Let's go!
Scram for the aircraft.

863
01:30:43,780 --> 01:30:46,161
Star!
Star, go!

864
01:30:54,645 --> 01:30:57,089
Star! Star!

865
01:30:57,302 --> 01:30:59,573
Star! Go back!
Come on!

866
01:30:59,608 --> 01:31:01,544
<i>Come on.
Come on.</i>

867
01:31:20,993 --> 01:31:21,876
What's your name?

868
01:31:22,414 --> 01:31:23,493
Kyle Reese.

869
01:31:29,274 --> 01:31:30,193
Stay with me!

870
01:31:51,025 --> 01:31:51,706
Back!

871
01:31:55,954 --> 01:31:56,804
Get back!

872
01:32:07,156 --> 01:32:08,518
Come on, Star,
move!

873
01:32:08,553 --> 01:32:09,155
Move!

874
01:32:37,209 --> 01:32:38,471
T-800s.

875
01:32:39,741 --> 01:32:41,204
There's so
many of them.

876
01:33:01,216 --> 01:33:01,965
Be careful!

877
01:33:06,936 --> 01:33:09,403
- What are these?
- Fuel cells.

878
01:33:09,952 --> 01:33:11,687
Life source
for the T-800.

879
01:33:14,937 --> 01:33:15,941
Nuclear.

880
01:33:17,290 --> 01:33:18,959
Enough
to level this place.

881
01:33:21,297 --> 01:33:22,264
Cover us.

882
01:33:23,537 --> 01:33:24,292
Get ready.

883
01:33:55,320 --> 01:33:56,424
Run!

884
01:33:57,713 --> 01:33:58,998
Star, come on!
Let's go!

885
01:34:01,156 --> 01:34:02,027
Come here!

886
01:34:05,795 --> 01:34:06,809
- Come on!
- Come on!

887
01:34:10,980 --> 01:34:12,569
We got to get
to the transport!

888
01:34:18,569 --> 01:34:19,531
Where are you going?

889
01:34:19,566 --> 01:34:21,144
- I gotta end this.
- No, no!

890
01:34:21,173 --> 01:34:22,268
I'm not gonna
leave you!

891
01:34:22,770 --> 01:34:25,326
- You didn't.
- Who are you?

892
01:34:26,138 --> 01:34:27,427
John Connor!

893
01:37:28,956 --> 01:37:31,128
- Hang back now!
- Hey!

894
01:37:31,163 --> 01:37:32,762
Hey, John Connor's
in there.

895
01:37:32,892 --> 01:37:33,394
Where?

896
01:37:33,425 --> 01:37:34,611
- You show me there.
- Hey, hey!

897
01:37:36,266 --> 01:37:36,812
What?

898
01:37:36,841 --> 01:37:38,258
John Connor's
in there.

899
01:37:39,247 --> 01:37:40,157
Come with me!

900
01:37:59,064 --> 01:37:59,968
Connor!

901
01:38:04,261 --> 01:38:05,551
I need help!

902
01:38:07,072 --> 01:38:07,947
Help!

903
01:38:09,739 --> 01:38:11,496
Connor, it's Kyle!
Help!

904
01:39:11,942 --> 01:39:13,986
You son of a bitch!

905
01:39:42,289 --> 01:39:43,586
Come on!

906
01:39:48,841 --> 01:39:50,061
Come on!

907
01:40:09,132 --> 01:40:10,491
Come on!

908
01:41:01,306 --> 01:41:02,505
Let's get
out of here.

909
01:41:20,633 --> 01:41:21,781
John...

910
01:41:26,804 --> 01:41:28,707
We can't make it
back to base.

911
01:41:28,736 --> 01:41:30,756
Center's down
and they never say so.

912
01:41:37,808 --> 01:41:40,672
<i>Medevac, urgent.
Severe chest trauma.</i>

913
01:41:41,180 --> 01:41:42,757
<i>Call the surgical team.</i>

914
01:41:43,115 --> 01:41:45,041
<i>We're locked.
It's Connor.</i>

915
01:43:04,454 --> 01:43:05,533
How long?

916
01:43:09,397 --> 01:43:12,037
His heart...

917
01:43:13,412 --> 01:43:14,379
can't take it.

918
01:43:14,409 --> 01:43:15,877
He's going to be okay.

919
01:43:16,730 --> 01:43:18,636
He's going
to be okay, Kate.

920
01:43:18,637 --> 01:43:19,463
Kyle?

921
01:43:33,349 --> 01:43:34,147
Take it...

922
01:43:54,145 --> 01:43:55,326
You earned it.

923
01:44:14,871 --> 01:44:15,579
Kate...

924
01:44:22,298 --> 01:44:23,204
Take mine.

925
01:44:24,898 --> 01:44:25,961
Marcus?

926
01:44:29,984 --> 01:44:32,212
Everybody deserves
a second chance.

927
01:44:35,949 --> 01:44:37,013
This is mine.

928
01:45:34,972 --> 01:45:36,729
<i>What is it
that makes us human?</i>

929
01:45:39,240 --> 01:45:41,201
<i>It's not something
you can program.</i>

930
01:45:43,619 --> 01:45:45,419
<i>You can't put it
into a chip.</i>

931
01:45:47,641 --> 01:45:49,700
<i>It's the strength
of the human heart.</i>

932
01:45:51,041 --> 01:45:54,438
<i>The difference
between us and machines.</i>

933
01:45:55,765 --> 01:46:01,922
Transcript and V1.1 Edits: VeRdiKT
[SubScene.com]

934
01:46:14,043 --> 01:46:15,769
<i>There is a storm
on the horizon.</i>

935
01:46:16,268 --> 01:46:17,980
<i>A time of hardship
and pain.</i>

936
01:46:19,396 --> 01:46:20,783
<i>This battle
has been won,</i>

937
01:46:20,818 --> 01:46:23,886
<i>but the war against
the machines raises on.</i>
